    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25.14"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        28 Jul 57
                        Sunday
                    </dateline>
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">14</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Wings</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    Lackland Air Force Base
                        <lb/>
                    . . . . . . San Antonio, Texas
                </fw>
                    
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>An Airplane, printed under the text</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neighardt<sic>Neihardt</sic>,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Please excuse the stationary, I'm not at Lackland any longer, but Warren Air Base at Cheyenne, Wyoming. The country is really nice up here. It's cool at night and doesn't feel like it gets up to 80&#176;-90&#176; readings they say it does in the daytime. From<del/> the base here I can see the front ranges of the Rockies, some of the mountains have snow on them even now. When I go up on a little hill and look to the North and West I can see for miles and miles to the mountains and the sky rim. It's all grass and mountain and sky and cloud. I can certainly see why the Indian fought for that land. It's really beautiful. I think of parts and lives from the cycle nearly every day. I can visualize the Indian on these prairies, the crawl the Hugh Glass made, the Indian wars and the battles, it's all new to me, this country. I've wanted to see country like this before, but I never did. The military life is not real hard, but its silly, illogical and contradictory. You can't use your own head, and after five year<del/><add>s</add> of college it's different to say the least, I'll be glad to get back to home and my new wife, JoAnn, she was sure glad to see the Indian prayer garden, she had heard a lot of it. I enjoyed it too. I hope your wife and family are all doing real well. I'm only going to be in for six months so I'll be back to school the second semester. It'll be nice to be back with my wife at home and it will be nice to be back at school to, take it easy now, I'd like to hear from you if you have time. I'll see you second semester.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Truly yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Duane Kelly</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener> <p>Please send me the date of your 50th wedding anniversary.</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
